'''Infantophilia''' or '''nepiophilia''' (From Greek ''nepion'', "infant" + ''-philia'') is the primary sexual attraction of adults to very small children (usually defined as 0&ndash;3 years old).  This should not be confused with [[infantilism]] (autonepiophilia).

